Introduction
Abstract: This project aims to analyze daily sales data for a retail business to provide actionable insights into sales trends and customer behavior. By understanding these patterns, the business can optimize inventory, improve marketing strategies, and enhance overall sales performance.

Description of the Data and its Source
Data Source:

Daily sales transactions from the company's POS system.
Customer demographics and purchase history.
Promotional and marketing campaign data.
Business Understanding and Data Understanding
Business Understanding: Retail businesses need to understand sales trends and customer behavior to make informed decisions about inventory, marketing, and sales strategies. By analyzing daily sales data, the business can identify peak sales periods, customer preferences, and areas for improvement.

Data Understanding:

Sales Transactions: Date, Product ID, Quantity Sold, Total Sale Amount.
Customer Data: Customer ID, Age, Gender, Location, Purchase History.
Promotions: Promotion ID, Start Date, End Date, Discount Percentage.
Objectives and Success Criteria
Objectives:

Analyze daily sales trends to identify patterns and seasonal variations.
Segment customers based on purchasing behavior and demographics.
Develop recommendations for inventory management and marketing strategies.
Success Criteria:

Accurate identification of peak sales periods.
Effective customer segmentation that improves marketing strategy.
Practical recommendations for inventory management.
