Data Preparation
Data Preparation Processes:

Data Cleaning: Handling missing values, removing duplicates, correcting data types.
Data Transformation: Creating new features from existing data, normalizing numerical data.
Data Inspection: Visualizing data distributions, identifying outliers.
Modeling
Modeling Processes:

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA): Visualizing sales trends, customer demographics, and promotional impact.
Time Series Analysis: Using models like SARIMA and seasonal decomposition to analyze sales trends.
Customer Segmentation: Applying clustering algorithms (e.g., K-means) to segment customers.
Predictive Modeling: Building models to forecast future sales and customer demand.
Evaluation
Model Evaluation:

Metrics: Accuracy, precision, recall, AUC-ROC for classification models; RMSE for regression models.
Comparison: Comparing model performance against baseline models and previous results.
Deployment
Solution Deployment:

Implementation: Deploying the predictive models and analysis results to the business's decision-making processes.
Tools: Using dashboards (e.g., Power BI, Tableau) to visualize and share insights.